# NOC Whisperer — Cursor Rules

This project is the NOC Whisperer — a multi-agent alert correlation system.

Before writing any code:
1. Read @CONTEXT.md for architecture, data structures, agent contracts, and design decisions
2. Read @EXECUTION_PLAN.md for today's specific task and acceptance test
3. Implement exactly what the session specifies — no more, no less

Coding standards:
- Python 3.11+ with full type hints on all functions
- Dataclasses for all data structures (no dicts passed between agents)
- Every class must have a docstring
- Every public method must have a docstring
- Use mock MCP tools during development — never assume live OTel stack is running
- Handle all external API calls with try/except — return [] on failure, never crash
- Load config from yaml files — never hardcode values
- Load API keys from .env — never hardcode credentials

Testing:
- Every session ends with the acceptance test passing
- Run: python -c "from module import Class; print('OK')" as minimum smoke test
- Use in-memory SQLite (:memory:) for all incident store tests

One file per session — do not create files not listed in the current session task.
